An smartphone application for sending and receiving bitcoins.  For use on jailbroken iOS devices.

The main features are:

* It uses 2D barcode using the camera for transfering the bitcoin address of the receiver.
* Uses eWallet service for instant transfer of bitcoins, using minimal cpu-resources, bandwidth, memory and power for running
* Free to use.
* You can give money (bitcoins) to someone within a minute as long he/she have a android telephone
* You can very easly pay instant for a restaurant visit (no need to wait for confirmations)

The app uses an EWallet hosted on [[Instawallet]].

##History

The app was launched on April 26, 2012 (2.1).  On June 19, 2012 Apple removed the app from the App Store (2.2).

